q4rrV4xPQtnFg_FQQ1W2pSkDwh_GmlgvVB6P4R_DIBA5gOsaF6Y1wTF573c2hW7qeWeSGpabxofqtfhLaTLhUHzc_E6SMNyrbr0-auJ9ZfHOc1-PXBYidXN1b7VTx0fHOQXM39jP69JcTdKNiD20hf5to5ZYKSUVgQ2vn4xzO_LSaaPel_-0Ay-gQXXqHWi8wWyiW3DFpnpwAAL87kjk7QRD2rKbNxg10O_FB8id8oPbeMhO-Z1Mu_k372N1jcN8HB54mHhNO7WSHCqfkwqDTHKzxUmTkiRdYxrU2oMfkd3K1qTuCuYF1tWuPmQ3_SqdRruUD3-teW2pxzND0dSk_ZgaPDgF8hkng==\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering code style checks**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about the potential checkstyle for the code. Should class names avoid underscores? The existing package cglib.cglib_nodep seems fine. I think method names should use lowerCamelCase, and I want to make constants static final. I'm pondering whether a line length of 100 would be okay too. I wonder if Checkstyle prohibits wildcards—maybe it’s better to avoid those. I'll check if imports are sorted and possibly edit the build.gradle file to reflect these changes.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_N56RAPNM3WZrTpVVlqPYltN8|fc_0e6ab983e6cb0a45016a26b87563a48194ba95a6027f2e6e75\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/ReflectUtilsTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\\n\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.ClassWriter;\\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.MethodVisitor;\\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.Opcodes;\\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.ReflectUtils;\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class ReflectUtilsTest {\\n    private static final String GENER