        Opcodes.ACC_PUBLIC, \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"()V\\\", null, null);\\n        constructor.visitCode();\\n        constructor.visitVarInsn(Opcodes.ALOAD, 0);\\n        constructor.visitMethodInsn(Opcodes.INVOKESPECIAL, \\\"java/lang/Object\\\", \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"()V\\\");\\n        constructor.visitInsn(Opcodes.RETURN);\\n        constructor.visitMaxs(1, 1);\\n        constructor.visitEnd();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780923373481}, {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_ziewFN1Dcf58AYH6lRr1MVQx|fc_0d66b72db21a271d016a26bbed1adc8190a64d03022cc5c9ab\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n# If omitted, fallback resolution in org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle still uses\\n# environment variable GVM_TCK_LC and then this property.\\nlibrary.coordinates = cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2\\nlibrary.version = 2.2.2\\nmetadata.dir = cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780923373481}, {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_9emd8GmiYUuuvxvpWLivxnCI|fc_0d66b72db21a271d016a26bbed1b008190b15169682b946b39\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"rules\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"excludeClasses\\\": \\\"**\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"includeClasses\\\": \\\"net.sf.cglib.**\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780923373481}]}\n595:[thinking] I need to add a dedicated Java test for the AbstractClassLoader. There's no existing AbstractClassLoaderTest, so I’ll probably make it in the package cglib.cglib_nodep, since it should be top-level public. I might want to check if I need a public API, keeping in mind the public abstract nature of AbstractClassLoader.\n603:[thinking] To ensure I can still reach getResourceAsStream, I'll consider creating a custom ClassLoader to return runtime-generated bytecode. This approach also h