rator to transform input into the same class and does defineClass using bytes in the JVM. However, in native, defineClass isn’t supported, so I need to handle that in the tests. \\n\\nI should also make sure to cover lines like super.loadClass and findLoadedClass, remembering that loadClass always starts with findLoadedClass. For example, the name \\\"java.lang.String\\\" should bypass the filter, leading to a call to super.loadClass. Additionally, it seems class initialization might cover class$ initialization, making it necessary to load an accepted class to access getResource.\\n\\n**Investigating class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm considering that existing tests utilize net.sf.cglib.asm.AbstractClassLoader, which imports org.objectweb.asm. But wait, could the nodep jar have been relocated? I should check the compiled javap output to gather more details. Perhaps I can also look at the jar listing to clarify the situation. Checking these would help me understand the current structure and resolve any potential issues.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d66b72db21a271d016a26bbee6f9c819094fdfb0b479a1bed\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqJrwCLLnLa-0omfMD0lAzBOshtZ5PPF24m1-8Immy1kTtm5ekSzPGCpMbHCHGSDWW--Q_Nr-MDKLq9iJgF5kc9VfXlCsuoSAidGAvpYeB--YON6zpY3JHzKVzgwy-9pYGRZMtf-b-vgS3Qh3c9-Pb1MhEuhF6z_MpiNTseGz04D4jHnM-fu5X07ft0c7_kV6uI4tkZpicRnm-toMHsB7cc0rMKcTTkiVoIgJwtCtA2EnoaekOPltSvOZqzPzQjd12h8gePXPmmazTuqqKr-ijuQmIw-FycotbcwVAFAIrlSID22dazTmjJvgqJRmBMEnNnMR0A7QAkdli0HZlld1_F3dr9etmTtIxclCurvg22sYrvEn2A5iFuMg8XNM9kVKhDYSBdD3L_10q4b4V4SmGozgwvXBmAAS971pFPZcOsHvzRDvJCx-4i4hnLx_LPIKMWu6v7lpqir7beysbSvfzssJN6N0Kl6vY7vuwuuYOLw7sHIg94_i0l5fE-OAqKeUh9_gq-emBQa0wmJVKHCIb-g6f9uoQQ05arFRv_dXPhM5pP15zhSTeUsvtPhAhapvgLBPki5R8jK59wntFCc-6OZ63Ev6uPF0rYd8xfxoHahSkXsaYyNni7B0WQMBLOMAaGKHyDR6E4uqtSUhSNAtBbhXTbqxTqsFQgZRNFm2EDQxRRgg5XmBDbw9Fr6juhiFflqdgJv62asGuQhbToCIDU4OCgoOq_BcY6uiDF_uXq01zBpxP9QfpjE2sGyrAA9zyh8Betj4YVA