ght cover class$ initialization, making it necessary to load an accepted class to access getResource.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Investigating class loading issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering that existing tests utilize net.sf.cglib.asm.AbstractClassLoader, which imports org.objectweb.asm. But wait, could the nodep jar have been relocated? I should check the compiled javap output to gather more details. Perhaps I can also look at the jar listing to clarify the situation. Checking these would help me understand the current structure and resolve any potential issues.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_WHJdftMK4FRaA7zmw90xP38U|fc_0d66b72db21a271d016a26bc02a4cc8190bf852a2db9ef0830\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2 -name '*.gradle' -o -name 'build.gradle' -maxdepth 3 && find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2 -type f | head\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1811, \"output\": 888, \"cacheRead\": 14848, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 17547, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780923373484, \"responseId\": \"resp_0d66b72db21a271d016a26bbedcec88190a6a09126a3b653bb\"}}\n620:[tool-exec] start id=call_WHJdftMK4FRaA7zmw90xP38U|fc_0d66b72db21a271d016a26bc02a4cc8190bf852a2db9ef0830 name=bash args={\"command\": \"find tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2 -name '*.gradle' -o -name 'build.gradle' -maxdepth 3 && find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2 -type f | head\", \"timeout\": 10}\n623:  tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/settings.gradle\n624:  tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/.gradle\n625:  tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/build.gradle\n627:  tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/settings.gradle\n628:  tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.